          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " and now, the original title’s sequel. With the promise of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Dragon Quest 3",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " being remade in this style and interest shared of more HD-2D remakes to come, the visuals in ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Octopath Traveler 2",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is a clear indication as to how the approach can act as a platform for further graphical innovation. The colour and lighting are lucious, the 2D/3D juxtaposition provides for some unique pathfinding opportunities and overall, it just looks gobsmackingly captivating. Here’s to the future of HD-2D!",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
